Package: rddid
Title: Treatment-Effect Estimation in Regression-Discontinuity
    Difference-in-Discontinuities (RD-DID) Designs
Version: 0.2.1.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Dor", "Leventer", , "leventerdor@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000")),
    person("Daniel", "Nevo", role = "aut"))
Description: Estimation and inference for the regression-discontinuity
    difference-in-discontinuities (RD-DID) design of Leventer and Nevo,
    which recovers a causal effect when a confounding policy switches at the
    same cutoff as the treatment of interest. The discontinuity is estimated
    period by period with standard local-linear RD and aggregated across
    periods following the identification result. Variances are provided for
    three sampling schemes (repeated cross-section, panel with time-constant
    running variable, panel with time-varying running variable), and the
    common bandwidth can be chosen either per period (the Imbens-Kalyanaraman
    / CCT within-period MSE-optimal rule) or jointly to minimise the
    asymptotic MSE of the aggregate estimator.
